50|$|The Penal law made fugitives of the {{remaining}} clerics, and {{they were forced to}} conduct ceremonies in secret, and in remote locations. Nighttime worship at Mass rocks became common. The attending priest would usually wear a veil, so that if an attendee was questioned, they were <b>able</b> <b>to</b> <b>say</b> truthfully <b>that</b> they did not know who had said the Mass.|$|R
