6000|$|Avoid this sin, and all sins. Let no man be <b>able</b> <b>to</b> <b>say</b> <b>that</b> {{you have}} {{defrauded}} him, {{that you have}} tyrannized over him; that you have neglected to do your duty by him. Let no man be <b>able</b> <b>to</b> <b>say</b> <b>that</b> you have rewarded him evil for evil. If possible, let him not be <b>able</b> <b>to</b> <b>say</b> <b>that</b> you have even lost your temper with him. Be generous; be forgiving. If you have an opportunity, be like David, and help him who without a cause is your enemy; and then {{you will have a}} right to say, like David, 'Give sentence with me, O Lord, according to my righteousness, and according to the cleanness of my hands in thy sight.' ...|$|E
